not likely - once the Rage-flood clears, this will be the limiting factor, making it just one cleric epic a day.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> 1. Need a few freinds to get there first of all.<br>
2. Firegiants seem to just aggro at will and wipe the camp.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
You need one person to get you there - a meatshield of some type.  If you want to be nice, bring along  a porter to get him out.<br>
<br>
The fire giants aggro if you get too close to the spawn point and then someone draws them without doing damage to them.  You have a number of options<br>
<br>
A- melee the giant - if you kill him you have bragging rights for a while.<br>
B- try and poof him in the lava - they SAY that they wont come thru the lava for you, and will go back to thier bind.  <br>
C- Move to where they WON'T aggro, take the death, walk over from your bind location (you DID bind closeby, right?) and rez yourself.  <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> 3. Who the hell wants to spend 72 hours or more camping this PoS turn in NPC.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I thought he'd been changed to a 24 hour spawn... but even 72 isn't a problem if you know the right friends...  hint - make friends with one or more 50+ monks and give them your telephone number.  You may get a telephone call like I'd did ( but mine was from a guildmate) <p>Belhaven<BR>
